OL,3,C'Your selfishness killed man son':
OL,4,CDad's anger at drink driver
OL,6,F"Simply and horrifically, you drove
OL,7,Fover Adam. I do not find you knew it
OL,8,Fwas a person, but the fact you drove
OL,9,Fon obliviously demonstrates how badly
OL,10,Faffected by drink you were."
OL,12,FAddressing Mr Cunliffe's family, Judge
OL,13,FMenary said: "The loss of Adam will
OL,14,Firretrievably damage all of your lives.
OL,16,F"The sentence I pass will not equate
OL,17,Fto your loss and suffering. The
OL,18,Freality is there is nothing this court
OL,19,Fcan do to alleviate your suffering."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/12
